<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910122-0064</DOCNO><DOCID>910122-0064.</DOCID><HL>   Who's News:   Montgomery Ward   Selects Daniel Levy   To Be Vice Chairman</HL><DATE>01/22/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C10</SO><CO>   WNEWS</CO><IN>BROADLINE RETAILERS, DEPARTMENT STORES (RTB)</IN><LP>   CHICAGO -- Montgomery Ward andamp; Co. named Daniel H. Levy tothe new post of vice chairman and chief operating officer,signaling that the retailer is entering a new phase.   Bernard Brennan, the company's chairman and chiefexecutive officer, said he chose a second in command nowbecause he wants to focus on possible acquisitions. &quot;With thecondition of the retail industry today and the number ofretailers who are suffering financially,&quot; he said, &quot;we shouldbe exploring external methods of growing our company.&quot;</LP><TEXT>   Mr. Brennan, who is widely credited with turning thecompany around before leading a management buy-out in 1988,said Montgomery Ward just &quot;concluded another record year ofearnings. We've gone through the turnaround, the leveragedbuy-out and now we're moving to the growth stage in thecompany,&quot; Mr. Brennan added.   Mr. Levy, 47 years old, formerly was president of thecompany's apparel and home group.</TEXT></DOC>